The EFF and ANC want the DA booted out, and are bringing motions of no confidence against Mayor Stevens Mokgalapa, and the speaker. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Chaos has once again erupted in the Tshwane Council chambers. The EFF and ANC have walked out of a council meeting bringing no-confidence motions against the metro's leadership. READ: Tshwane leadership battle delayed The  Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Department says the city should be placed under administration if it doesn't get its house in order. The EFF and ANC are attempting to remove mayor Stevens Mokgalapa and speaker Katlego Mathebe and a host of other officials through fresh no-confidence motions. In December, the High Court in Pretoria granted the DA an application for a review of Mokgalapa and Mathebe's removal.